LOC=/etc/passwd
WHY=Authentication
DES="provides the local user database
When shadow passwords is installed, which is is by default,
passwords are not stored in
/etc/passwd
Instead passwords are stored in
/etc/shadow
However,
/etc/passwd
does contain user account information

There are tools for safely editing it
But occasionally SAs edit it manually.
Account  0 is root
Accounts 1 through 255 are for device node modes.
Accounts 256 through 511 are for daemons and services.
Accounts 512 through 1023 are reserved.
Accounts 1024 through 65534 are for users.
Account  65535 is for nobody."

MAN="5 passwd"
